communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the DC Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

The Computer-Aided Dispatch (CAD) event history/chronology and unit history for CCN 24170107, single vehicle crash at Constitution Ave NW & 3rd St NW, Washington, D.C., on November 1, 2024. Please include:

-All time-stamped entries (“remarks”)
-Unit dispatch/arrive/clear times
-Any cross-referenced event numbers and associated histories
-Final disposition/closure codes
-Any attachments normally included with CAD histories (e.g., narrative notes, location updates)

If feasible within your search parameters, please indicate whether any CAD remarks or event history entries reference the presence of any other road users on bicycles, separate from the injured party (D-2). I am not requesting personal identifiers for any such individual.

If MPD is not the custodian, please transfer this request or advise me to re-file with the correct agency.

I am not seeking personal identifiers; please redact such information as needed.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 15 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Patrik Szigeti
